</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1058,1374,1425]" pageId="47" pageNumber="1192">
E t y m o l o g y: Thetrivialname, 
<emphasis box="[529,615,1374,1395]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="1192">petalosa</emphasis>
, is a Latin adjective that stems from 
<emphasis box="[985,1058,1374,1395]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="1192">petalus</emphasis>
(= broad), with reference to the comparatively broadened phallobasic lobes.
</paragraph>
